This solution works by first determining the first and last occurrence of each character in the string. It then expands these occurrences into valid substrings that contain all occurrences of each character within their range. After finding all such intervals, it sorts them by their end positions to ensure the earliest ending substrings are chosen first. Finally, it selects non-overlapping intervals to maximize the number of substrings while ensuring the total length is minimized.
